message:
{{#is_alert}}
@pagerduty-NeuroQuest-Backend

**The device-signature signed-login pass rate has drifted below the SLO.**

Over the last 4 hours the sample-scaled pass rate `(ok / sample_rate) / ((ok / sample_rate) + rejected)` fell below the critical threshold (98%). The healthy baseline is ~99.8%, so this signals a SLOW erosion — a gradual climb in rejections, or one route/enforcement mode quietly degrading — rather than the sudden active-install spike the `device-signature-lockout` monitor catches. The two alerts are complementary: lockout pages on an abrupt cliff in a 15m window; this one pages on a multi-hour slide that would otherwise only be visible to someone staring at the dashboard.

**INVESTIGATE:**
1. Open the **device-signature pass rate** dashboard (`artifacts/api-server/docs/dashboards/device-signature-pass-rate.json`) — the *Pass-rate trend by route* and *by enforcement mode (hard_mode)* tiles, plus the *route × hard_mode* table, show WHICH route or mode is dragging the ratio down.
2. Check for a recent deploy touching `artifacts/api-server/src/lib/deviceAuth.ts` (shared verify / sampling) or the mobile signer `artifacts/neuro-quest-mobile/lib/userAuth.ts`.

**EMERGENCY ROLLBACK (general per-:id gate, no redeploy needed):**
Set the secret `DEVICE_AUTH_SOFT_MODE=1` on the `api-server` deployment to return `requireDeviceSignature` to verify-and-log-without-reject, so members stop getting 401s while you investigate. NOTE: the strict GDPR (`requireDeviceSignatureStrict`) and IAP (`requireUserOrDevice`) gates intentionally IGNORE soft mode — if the drift is concentrated on export/erasure/purchase routes, the only mitigation is reverting the offending build. See .agents/memory/device-signature-enforcement.md.
{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_warning}}
Device-signature pass rate has slipped below the warning threshold (99%) over the last 4h — watch the dashboard; it is trending toward the SLO breach.
{{/is_warning}}
{{#is_recovery}}
Device-signature pass rate has recovered back above the SLO threshold.
{{/is_recovery}}
